1> My alt is a level 18 Ranger.  I have the hide and sneak skills.  Should I develop them?  Will I be able to use them for corpse runs like Rogues do?  Or is gaining skills here just a waste of time.<br>
<br>
Josey - Cleric<br>
Jakki - Ranger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stupie>stupie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 375<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 9:59:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelflame.com/ranger/signitures/stupiesilverthorn[1].gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> I have both skills maxed, I use them now and then. Easy to max out, something to do when waiting on that rezz.....you can use them when medding too, so i would hit sneak and hide and then hit them off, when they refresh, repeat...<br>
hide is like camo, some mobs will see through it some wont, good for sittign in EC and not being asked for sows and ports every 2 secs.<br>
Sneak is good for some quests, will turn you indifferent to all mobs from behind, so it lets you hand itmes into KOS mobs for quests or use merchants if your faction is not high enough.<br>
That bow i got in Kael not long ago I got from using sneak, so it comes in handy.<br>
I'm no expert on any of this, so I may be missing some stuff here....hope this helps.... <p>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11063" target="_blank"><img border="1" src="http://www.angelflame.com/ranger/signitures/stupiesilverthorn[1].gif" width="151" height="347">







</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stupie>stupie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/3/01 9:59:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ubenadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 10:39:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> You cannot move while hiding, unless you use sneak. <br>
If you try to sneak then hide you only get one attampt at it, but if you hide then sneak you can attempt to sneak repeatedly.<br>
<br>
I have been learning alot about these skills exploring the hole. lol <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/utivorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tivorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 11:22:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> Once you have skill over 100 in hide and sneak they never fail anymore. mobs can see through hide, but nothing (not even gods) sees through sneak when you are behind the mob.<br>
<br>
--<br>
Tivorr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ujoseydm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Josey DM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 1:44:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> ok, more questions.<br>
<br>
When I had a low level Rogue I could hide and sneak at the same time.  With my Ranger, however, my hide only works if I don't move, even when I successfully sneak (at least I assume it's successful cuz I go very slow).  Also when I'm successful at sneak and con a mob, sometimes it's &quot;indifferent&quot; and sometimes it's &quot;ready to attack&quot; depending on when I con it.  Is there a pattern I'm missing?  I was very impressed by Tivorrs abilities in CR's and would like to develop this skill in my Ranger if at all possible.  All advice is greatly appriciated.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Josey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amanar>Amanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orc Pawn</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 2:56:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> Josey...sneak has to be behind the mob no matter what...and when it scowls at you that means it failed. Us rangers don't get fail messages, so you just gotta wait to see if the button repops or not. They are very useful abilities i use them both all the time. Getting into KC is not fun with the two guys at the entrance that see invis, solution, sneak and run behind em. I hide all the time while medding...or once when i went LD in the middle of Splitpaw i came back, and before stuff had a chance to aggro i clicked hide and waited for drendar to come help out. But we can't hide and sneak at the same time like rogues...although we can sneak behind guys...then when they are about to turn around stop and click hide. But we'll never be very effective on CRs.<br>
<br>
Amanar 53 Pathfinder<br>
<br>
Maxo 17 Gnome Warrior<br>
<br>
Waxo 9 Gnome Cleric<br>
<br>
Zaxo 4 Gnome Enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/usilvermink.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvermink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 4:50:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> As far as never failing over 100, Rangers hide and sneak max out at 75.<br>
<br>
Kenolein 46 Ranger<br>
Atdaar 41 Wizard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/usilvenstar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvenstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 11:29:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> As a druid, I have the ability to hide and sneak also. I find using hide best when I am root, dotting and want to med while my dots do their work so no wanderers will attack me. What you need to do is hit your hide button, con whatever is close and if it cons indifferent it means you have successfullly hidden. I sometimes have to try and hide 3 or 4 times before I get it to work. This also works well in dungeons, it seems those wee beasties love to hit medding druids. <br>
<br>
<br>
Xarx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=seb>seb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 9:08:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Hide and Sneak</span><hr size=1> Sneak is nice if you are in RE. Use sneak on the vendors and you can sell to them.<br>
<br>
